paragraph.content:
contain information that is false, misleading or deceptive as to a material
                    fact, or is false, misleading or deceptive through omission of a material
                    fact;

contain any express or implied remarks or comments that are adverse to any
                    other notary public or firm, whether by way of a comparison of services,
                    practice or fees or otherwise;

expressly or impliedly represent that a notary public or firm has expertise
                    in carrying out notarial work in general or a particular area of notarial
                    work;

contain, without the prior written consent of a client, a description
                    sufficient to enable the client or a particular item of the client’s business to
                    be identified;

be calculated to cause, or carried out in such manner as to likely to
                    cause, injury, discomfort, annoyance or inconvenience to any recipient or
                    intended recipient;
